This month so far has been a rollercoaster….

It’s been really fun to develop this art for Sweet One with @laceyfree and @marc_santarromana and to watch it grow into one of the best parties and cultural nights I’ve seen in LA in a long time. One day we’ll have a gallery show with all these dope drawings and amazing photos. Always great to be creative with great people and a great team…thank you @kiar.e @keithpowers

Sometimes it feels like the world’s on my shoulders. “Window”
#newmusic 🎥 @nicholasjandora
You never know what personal battle someone is going thru. A reminder for all of us to look out for one another.

The #1 rule I made for myself when I got in this business was to only work with people I would have a meal with on the weekends and I could call my friends. Thank you God for allowing me to stick to that rule and then some. I love my people.
Thank you for everyone for streaming, sending me messages, spreading the word and taking a moment to show this music some love. Grateful, grateful, grateful.

One of the big lessons I’ve learned is to make the best music you also have to get out of the studio and find inspiration. Hang out with great people that inspire you, eat good food, go look at art…whatever gives you what you need! Some of the best ideas happen while you’re just living life.

Took my Moms out for her bday and she said she wanted to try some new things. It’s never too late for first times so here’s how it went. 
1. First time at Manuela (she’s picky about her food and restaurants) - loved it, loved her Bloody Mary specifically. 
2. First time trying a new salad (it was arugula, nectarines, goat cheese, and pecans. - her exact words “who puts fruit in salad, goat cheese is weird, take these almonds”.
3. First time going to the Broad museum - loved it, her favorites were Roy Lichtenstein and Jeff Koons. 
A great day and always fun to do new things with your mom.

I’ve never been a big Bday person but when you have friends like I have, they really make you feel appreciated. Also thank you to all my friends for the calls and messages. You all lift my spirits up and really make me appreciate it all the blessings I have in this life. Love.

Just a friendly reminder to all of us…

We’ve been working on putting together an art show for a minute and the time has come! Many people don’t know that I actually started as a visual artist and then got into music which took off.  Now that we are in the age of doing it allI I’ve gotten back into painting and it’s become a big inspiration to my music creation as well and with the push from some of my closest people it felt like it was time to start to put these paintings out into the world. So thank you @laceyfree for yelling at me to paint and @lindseyseason for getting my first real work, thank you @benhereandthere for the guidance into the art world and doing this show with me, thank you @marc_santarromana for making me feel bad for@not showing my work 😂 and thank you @mikeroto for always giving me sparks and ideas. And I’m a little nervous so please come to my show!!! (Here’s all the invites we made!)
